{
  // A tree node — a kernel Thought carrying its `depth` and (except the root) a `parent` ref. The
  // thought `text` is prose-terminal; the raw `score` (when the external judge wrote one) is snapped
  // by the kernel's Scored/Score::band — every gate downstream keys on the band, never the float.
  // Named TreeNode, not "Node": Node/Segment are the pre-set ROOT FACTS the concept system anchors
  // on via `require` (the Vertice/Edge pattern) — a concept NAMED like a root fact while carrying
  // conditions maps at instant zero, before its requires (Thought here) resolve, and its children
  // are never descended (the linted `engine-marker-name` trap, paid once here).
  "require": ["Thought", "depth"]
}
